mbol","association":"significant","population":"American (Caucasian)","variants":"rs2590504","pubmedId":22533364,"pubmedUrl":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22533364/"}],"genAgeHuman":null,"genAgeMouse":[],"organAge":[]}},"RNR2":{"symbol":"RNR2","annotation":{"approvedName":"RNA, ribosomal 45S cluster 2","hgncId":"HGNC:10083","chromosomeLocation":"14p12 not on reference assembly","chromosome":"14","locusGroup":"non-coding RNA","locusType":"RNA, cluster","humanEntrezId":"6053","ensemblGeneId":null,"uniprotIds":[],"aliases":[],"previousSymbols":[],"hgncUrl":"https://www.genenames.org/data/gene-symbol-report/#!/hgnc_id/HGNC%3A10083","ncbiMapLocation":"14p12","ncbiChromosome":"14","ncbiUrl":"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/6053"},"mouseOrtholog":{"homologyClassId":"51825133","humanSymbol":"RNR2","humanEntrezId":"4550","humanHgncId":"HGNC:7471","humanLocation":"ChrMT","humanCoordinatesGrch38":"ChrMT:1671-3229(+)","mouseSymbol":"mt-Rnr2","mouseEntrezId":"17725","mouseMgiId":"MGI:102492","mouseLocation":"ChrMT syntenic","mouseCoordinatesGrcm39":"ChrMT:1094-2675(+)","mappingType":"one-to-one","source":"MGI/Alliance homology report","sourceUrl":"https://www.informatics.jax.org/downloads/reports/HOM_MouseHumanSequence.rpt"},"summary":"45S ribosomal DNA (rDNA) arrays, or clusters, are present on human chromosomes 13, 14, 15, 21 and 22, designated RNR1 through RNR5, respectively. Each cluster consists of multiple 45S rDNA repeat units that vary in number among individuals and chromosomes, with total diploid copy number estimates ranging from 60 to >800 repeat units in a human genome. The 45S rDNA repeat unit encodes a 45S rRNA precursor, transcribed by RNA polymerase I, which is processed to form the 18S, 5.8S and 28S rRNAs. Gene and RefSeq, in collaboration with HGNC, currently describe one 45S rDNA cluster, and one set of 45S precursor and product rRNAs, for each of the five human chromosomes to which these loci are localized. This gene represents the 45S ribosomal DNA cluster on chromosome 14. [provided by RefSeq, Feb 2017]","summarySource":{"label":"NCBI Gene","url":"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/6053","humanEntrezId":"6053"},"coverage":{"publicSourceCount":1,"publicSources":["longevityMap"],"evidenceLayerCount":1,"evidenceLayers":[{"key":"genomics","sources":["LongevityMap"]}],"organisms":["Human"],"transcriptomicContexts":[],"endpoints":["Longevity"]},"statistics":{"totalEvidenceRecords":1,"transcriptomicRecords":0,"transcriptomicPositive":0,"transcriptomicNegative":0,"epigeneticAgeCpGs":0,"epigeneticMortalityCpGs":0,"epigeneticMortalitySensitivitySupported":0,"longevityAssociations":1,"genAgeHumanRecords":0,"genAgeMouseRecords":0,"organAgeProteinOrganRecords":0,"organAgeOrgans":[],"bestReportedP":null},"evidence":{"transcriptomic":[],"epigeneticAge":[],"epigeneticMortality":[],"longevityMap":[{"recordId":"longevity:354","sourceKey":"longevityMap","sourceFile":"longevity.csv","sourceRow":350,"reportId":"354","sourceSymbol":"RNR2","symbolMapping":"approved_symbol","association":"significant","population":"Japanese","variants":"Mt3010G/A","pubmedId":9449878,"pubmedUrl":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9449878/"}],"genAgeHuman":null,"genAgeMouse":[],"organAge":[]}},"SULT1A1":{"symbol":"SULT1A1","annotation":{"approvedName":"sulfotransferase family 1A member 1","hgncId":"HGNC:11453","chromosomeLocation":"16p11.2","chromosome":"16","locusGroup":"protein-coding gene","locusType":"gene with protein product","humanEntrezId":"6817","ensemblGeneId":"ENSG00000196502","uniprotIds":["P50225"],"aliases":["P-PST"],"previousSymbols":["STP","STP1"],"hgncUrl":"https://www.genenames.org/data/gene-symbol-report/#!/hgnc_id/HGNC%3A11453","ncbiMapLocation":"16p11.2","ncbiChromosome":"16","ncbiUrl":"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/6817"},"mouseOrtholog":null,"summary":"Sulfotransferase enzymes catalyze the sulfate conjugation of many hormones, neurotransmitters, drugs, and xenobiotic compounds. These cytosolic enzymes are different in their tissue distributions and substrate specificities. The gene structure (number and length of exons) is similar among family members. This gene encodes one of two phenol sulfotransferases with thermostable enzyme activity.  Multiple alternatively spliced variants that encode two isoforms have been identified for this gene. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008]","summarySource":{"label":"NCBI Gene","url":"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/6817","humanEntrezId":"6817"},"coverage":{"publicSourceCount":1,"publicSources":["longevityMap"],"evidenceLayerCount":1,"evidenceLayers":[{"key":"genomics","sources":["LongevityMap"]}],"organisms":["Human"],"transcriptomicContexts":[],"endpoints":["Longevity"]},"statistics":{"totalEvidenceRecords":1,"transcriptomicRecords":0,"transcriptomicPositive":0,"transcriptomicNegative":0,"epigeneticAgeCpGs":0,"epigeneticMortalityCpGs":0,"epigeneticMortalitySensitivitySupported":0,"longevityAssociations":1,"genAgeHumanRecords":0,"genAgeMouseRecords":0,"organAgeProteinOrganRecords":0,"organAgeOrgans":[],"bestReportedP":null},"evidence":{"transcriptomic":[],"epigeneticAge":[],"epigeneticMortality":[],"longevityMap":[{"recordId":"longevity:29","sourceKey":"longevityMap","sourceFile":"longevity.csv","sourceRow":28,"reportId":"29","sourceSymbol":"SULT1A1","symbolMapping":"approved_symbol","association":"significant","population":"English (Caucasian) and Nigerian","variants":"638G/A","pubmedId":9854023,"pubmedUrl":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9854023/"}],"genAgeHuman":null,"genAgeMouse":[],"organAge":[]}},"TAF1":{"symbol":"TAF1","annotation":{"approvedName":"TATA-box binding protein associated factor 1","hgncId":"HGNC:11535","chromosomeLocation":"Xq13.1","chromosome":"X","locusGroup":"protein-coding gene","locusType":"gene with protein product","humanEntrezId":"6872","ensemblGeneId":"ENSG00000147133","uniprotIds":["P21675"],"aliases":["NSCL2","TAFII250","KAT4","DYT3/TAF1"],"previousSymbols":["TAF2A","BA2R","CCG1","CCGS","DYT3"],"hgncUrl":"https://www.genenames.org/data/gene-symbol-report/#!/hgnc_id/HGNC%3A11535","ncbiMapLocation":"Xq13.1","ncbiChromosome":"X","ncbiUrl":"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/6872"},"mouseOrtholog":null,"summary":"Initiation of transcription by RNA polymerase II requires the activities of more than 70 polypeptides. The protein that coordinates these activities is the basal transcription factor TFIID, which binds to the core promoter to position the polymerase properly, serves as the scaffold for assembly of the remainder of the transcription complex, and acts as a channel for regulatory signals. TFIID is composed of the TATA-binding protein (TBP) and a group of evolutionarily conserved proteins known as TBP-associated factors or TAFs. TAFs may participate in basal transcription, serve as coactivators, function in promoter recognition or modify general transcription factors (GTFs) to facilitate complex assembly and transcription initiation. This gene encodes the largest subunit of TFIID. This subunit binds to core promoter sequences encompassing the transcription start site. It also binds to activators and other transcriptional regulators, and these interactions affect the rate of transcription initiation. This subunit contains two independent protein kinase domains at the N- and C-terminals, but also possesses acetyltransferase activity and can act as a ubiquitin-activating/conjugating enzyme. Mutations in this gene result in Dystonia 3, torsion, X-linked, a dystonia-parkinsonism disorder. Alternative splicing of this gene results in multiple transcript variants. This gene is part of a complex transcription unit (TAF1/DYT3), wherein some transcript variants share exons with TAF1 as well as additional downstream DYT3 exons. [provided by RefSeq, Oct 2013]","summarySource":{"label":"NCBI Gene","url":"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/6872","humanEntrezId":"6872"},"coverage":{"publicSourceCount":1,"publicSources":["genAge"],"evidenceLayerCount":1,"evidenceLayers":[{"key":"genomics","sources":["GenAge"]}],"organisms":["Human"],"transcriptomicContexts":[],"endpoints":["Longevity"]},"statistics":{"totalEvidenceRecords":1,"transcriptomicRecords":0,"transcriptomicPositive":0,"transcriptomicNegative":0,"epigeneticAgeCpGs":0,"epigeneticMortalityCpGs":0,"epigeneticMortalitySensitivitySupported":0,"longevityAssociations":0,"genAgeHumanRecords":1,"genAgeMouseRecords":0,"organAgeProteinOrganRecords":0,"organAgeOrgans":[],"bestReportedP":null},"evidence":{"transcriptomic":[],"epigeneticAge":[],"epigeneticMortality":[],"longevityMap":[],"genAgeHuman":{"recordId":"genage:human:180","sourceKey":"genAge","sourceFile":"genage_human.csv","sourceRow":180,"organism":"Human","genAgeId":180,"sourceSymbol":"TAF1","symbolMapping":"approved_symbol","geneName":"TAF1 RNA polymerase II, TATA box binding protein (TBP)-associated factor, 250kDa","entrezGeneId":6872,"uniprotEntry":"TAF1_HUMAN","evidenceBasis":["downstream"]},"genAgeMouse":[],"organAge":[]}}}
